<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="294" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,687,1613]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,687,712]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Fastigium of vertex elongated, slender and horizontally directed, dorsally with lateral furrows with tubercles. Eyes small and rounded, located in the inferior and lateral part of antennal cavities. Lateral lobes of pronotum with humeral sinus moderately pronounced. Both sexes brachypterous, males with tegmina covering first segment and females the second, posterior wings vestigial. Tenth tergite not modified, male cerci divided, with dorsal branch flattened and ventral one thin, not flat. Ovipositor longer than body, slender, without serrations.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,957,868,893]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,687,1613]" box="[199,957,868,893]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,868,893]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<typeStatus box="[199,258,868,893]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Monzón-Sierra &amp; Cortés-Torres, 2016" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Monzón-Sierra &amp; Cortés-Torres" authorityYear="2016" box="[361,685,868,893]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mayacephalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dickmanorum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[361,685,868,893]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Mayacephalus dickmanorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[692,755,868,893]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[692,755,868,893]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, described below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="294" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,687,1613]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,903,928]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Etymology.</emphasis>
The first part of the name of this genus is for the Mayan culture that inhabits southern 
<collectingRegion box="[1303,1389,903,928]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<collectingCountry box="[1303,1389,903,928]" name="Mexico" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Mexico</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
and northern Central America. The second part of the name – 
<emphasis box="[809,909,940,965]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">cephalus</emphasis>
is common in various names of genera in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1838" box="[151,332,975,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Conocephalinae">Conocephalinae</taxonomicName>
subfamily.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,687,1613]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,1012,1037]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Comparison.</emphasis>
This new genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Chamorro-Rengifo &amp; Braun, 2010" authorityName="Chamorro-Rengifo &amp; Braun" authorityYear="2010" box="[679,1204,1012,1037]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Toledopizia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[679,809,1012,1037]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Toledopizia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chamorro-Rengifo, J. &amp; Braun, H." box="[815,1204,1012,1037]" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" pagination="41 - 66" part="2635" refString="Chamorro-Rengifo, J. &amp; Braun, H. (2010) The Tettigoniidae (Orthoptera) described by Salvador de Toledo Piza Jr. and deposited in the collection of the University of Sao Paulo, Escola Superior de Agricultura &quot; Luiz de Queiroz &quot;, Brazil. Zootaxa, 2635, 41 - 66." title="The Tettigoniidae (Orthoptera) described by Salvador de Toledo Piza Jr. and deposited in the collection of the University of Sao Paulo, Escola Superior de Agricultura &quot; Luiz de Queiroz &quot;, Brazil" type="journal article" year="2010">Chamorro-Rengifo &amp; Braun, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Serville, 1831" authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Copiphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1214,1335,1012,1037]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Copiphora</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Serville, J. G. A." journalOrPublisher="Annales des Sciences Naturelles" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" pagination="28 - 292" part="22" refString="Serville, J. G. A. (1831) Revue methodique des insectes de l'ordre des Orthopteres. Annales des Sciences Naturelles, 22 (86), 28 - 292." title="Revue methodique des insectes de l'ordre des Orthopteres" type="journal article" year="1831">Serville, 1831</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Uvarov, 1940" authorityName="Uvarov" authorityYear="1940" box="[270,577,1047,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Daedalellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[270,405,1047,1072]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Daedalellus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Uvarov, B. P." box="[417,577,1048,1072]" journalOrPublisher="Annals and Magazine of Natural History, London, 11" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" pagination="173 - 176" part="5" publicationUrl="http://dx.doi.org/10.1080/00222934008527035" refString="Uvarov, B. P. (1940) Twenty-eight new generic names in Orthoptera. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, London, 11 (5), 173 - 176. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222934008527035" title="Twenty-eight new generic names in Orthoptera" type="journal article" year="1940">Uvarov, 1940</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The similarity with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chamorro-Rengifo &amp; Braun" authorityYear="2010" box="[826,956,1047,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Toledopizia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[826,956,1047,1072]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Toledopizia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uvarov" authorityYear="1940" box="[1019,1154,1047,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Daedalellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1019,1154,1047,1072]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Daedalellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is for its brachypterous condition; from the first genus it can be distinguished by the shape of the pronotum, and that in the new genus the humeral sinus is visible, pronotal disc with well developed furrows, external genicular lobules from anterior and medial femora unarmed; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chamorro-Rengifo &amp; Braun" authorityYear="2010" box="[439,569,1156,1181]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Toledopizia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[439,569,1156,1181]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Toledopizia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with pronotal furrows and humeral sinus not developed, all genicular lobes are armed; male of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Piza, 1980)" authorityName="Piza" authorityYear="1980" baseAuthorityName="Piza" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[368,811,1191,1216]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Toledopizia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salesopolensis">
<emphasis box="[368,667,1191,1216]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Toledopizia salesopolensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Piza Jr., S. T." box="[682,802,1191,1216]" journalOrPublisher="Revista de Agricultura (Piracicaba), 55" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" pagination="111 - 114" part="3" refString="Piza Jr., S. T. (1980) Dois novos copiforineos do Brasil (Orthoptera - Tettigoniidae). Revista de Agricultura (Piracicaba), 55 (3), 111 - 114." title="Dois novos copiforineos do Brasil (Orthoptera - Tettigoniidae)" type="journal article" year="1980">Piza, 1980</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is not known so that comparison is not possible.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="294" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,687,1613]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<taxonomicName authority="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Monzón-Sierra &amp; Cortés-Torres, 2016" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Monzón-Sierra &amp; Cortés-Torres" authorityYear="2016" box="[199,362,1228,1253]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mayacephalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[199,362,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Mayacephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[375,459,1228,1253]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[375,459,1228,1253]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">n. gen.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uvarov" authorityYear="1940" box="[632,767,1228,1253]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Daedalellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[632,767,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Daedalellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having head and fastigium extraordinarily elongated (fastigium five or six times as long as antennal scape), pronotum three times longer than wide, metazona covering stridulatory area, male cerci branches asymmetrical, cerci dorso-ventrally divided, dorsal branch wide and flattened. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uvarov" authorityYear="1940" box="[263,398,1335,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Daedalellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[263,398,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Daedalellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with head and fastigium moderately elongate (fastigium less than three times antennal scape length), pronotum 1.5 times as long as wide, not covering stridulatory area, branches of male cercus slender, similarly shaped and divided in the latero-internal margin of cercus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,687,1613]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
The proposed new genus can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1831" box="[818,940,1444,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Copiphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[818,940,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Copiphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly by the development of the wings, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Monzón-Sierra &amp; Cortés-Torres, 2016" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Monzón-Sierra &amp; Cortés-Torres" authorityYear="2016" box="[151,314,1479,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mayacephalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[151,314,1479,1504]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Mayacephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[324,405,1479,1504]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[324,405,1479,1504]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">n. gen.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is brachypterous and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1831" box="[668,789,1479,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Copiphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[668,789,1479,1504]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Copiphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is macropterous. The shape of the fastigium in the new genus is similar in shape to 
<taxonomicName authority="Saussure &amp; Pictet, 1898" authorityName="Saussure &amp; Pictet" authorityYear="1898" box="[503,1016,1516,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Copiphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azteca">
<emphasis box="[503,710,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Copiphora azteca</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Saussure, H. &amp; Pictet, A." box="[724,1016,1516,1541]" journalOrPublisher="Biologia Centrali-Americana" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" pagination="345 - 456" part="1" refString="Saussure, H. &amp; Pictet, A. (1898) Insecta Orthoptera (Orthoptera Genuina). Fam. Locustidae. Biologia Centrali-Americana, 1, 345 - 456." title="Insecta Orthoptera (Orthoptera Genuina). Fam. Locustidae" type="journal article" year="1898">Saussure &amp; Pictet, 1898</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Scudder, 1869" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1869" box="[1035,1342,1516,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Copiphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[1035,1160,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">C. gracilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Scudder, S. H." box="[1174,1342,1516,1541]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Boston Society of Natural History" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" pagination="330 - 345" part="12" refString="Scudder, S. H. (1869) Notes on Orthoptera collected by Prof. James Orton on either side of the Andes of Equatorial South America. Proceedings of the Boston Society of Natural History, 12, 330 - 345." title="Notes on Orthoptera collected by Prof. James Orton on either side of the Andes of Equatorial South America" type="journal article" year="1869">Scudder, 1869</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Serville, 1831" authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Copiphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicauda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">C. longicauda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Serville, J. G. A." box="[297,470,1551,1576]" journalOrPublisher="Annales des Sciences Naturelles" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" pagination="28 - 292" part="22" refString="Serville, J. G. A. (1831) Revue methodique des insectes de l'ordre des Orthopteres. Annales des Sciences Naturelles, 22 (86), 28 - 292." title="Revue methodique des insectes de l'ordre des Orthopteres" type="journal article" year="1831">Serville, 1831</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Mesotibiae dorsally armed with spines in 
<emphasis box="[1038,1166,1551,1576]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1831" box="[1038,1162,1551,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Copiphora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Copiphora</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
unarmed dorsally in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Monzón-Sierra &amp; Cortés-Torres" authorityYear="2016" box="[151,314,1588,1613]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mayacephalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,314,1588,1613]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Mayacephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
